    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Norman keeps, usually on the sites of older structures, and consisting of a stone wall on top of a motte, or steep mound. Within this wall, or shell, other buildings were contructed, using the wall as support, leaving an open courtyard in the center. A successor to the motte-and-bailey castle.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
